  "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nAfter upgrading Prysm to `v4.1.0`, we get the following response when querying for a non-existing slot block.\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ curl {server_url_4.1.0}/eth/v1/beacon/headers?slot=7679550\r\n{\"data\":[],\"execution_optimistic\":false,\"finalized\":true}\r\n```\r\n\r\nFor this example we used slot [7679550](https://beaconcha.in/slot/7679550) which is finalized, but does **not** include a block.\r\n\r\nThis is a breaking change, as the same API call in previous versions would return a 404 error.\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nUp to version `v4.0.8` we would receive a 404 error:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ curl {server_url_4.0.8}/eth/v1/beacon/headers?slot=7679550\r\n{\"message\":\"Could not find requested blocks\",\"code\":404}`\r\n```\r\n### Platform(s)\r\n\r\nLinux (x86)\r\n\r\n### What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)\r\n\r\nv4.1.0",
